      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm studying for my ml exam and im a bit stuck. can u explain the main difference between L1 and L2 regularization? specifically how they actually affect the model coefficients during training? thanks",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure! L1 and L2 regularization both help to prevent overfitting by penalizing large coefficients, but they do so in different ways. L1 regularization adds a penalty proportional to the absolute value of the coefficients, encouraging sparsity (i.e., some coefficients can become exactly zero). L2 regularization adds a penalty proportional to the square of the coefficients, which tends to distribute the penalty across all coefficients, shrinking them rather than making them zero. This leads to models where L2-regularized coefficients tend to be smaller but never exactly zero.",
